body:
@mktal please review these doc updates and merge.

The only software changes needed are:

1) move epsilon and eps_table into reg_params section of model summary table
2) implement on-line help for madlib.svm_predict();
3) please implement examples in on-line docs for:
- madlib.svm_classification('example');
- madlib.svm_regression('example');
- madlib.svm_predict('example');

4) add to model output table
- loss  FLOAT8. Value of the objective function of SVM. See Technical Background section below for more details.
- norm_of_gradient  FLOAT8. Value of the L2-norm of the (sub)-gradient of the objective function.

You may want to combine these with this pull request.

Related to
https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MADLIB-956

I have made some changes and added validation and online help functions (in my [private fork branch](https://github.com/iyerr3/incubator-madlib/commits/feature/pred_metrics_take2)). 

I have not implemented the SRF versions as discussed earlier. We can make those functions as a separate work. 

@orhankislal could you please pull in the 3 commits on that branch and update your branch to update this PR. Once we've discussed the changes here, I can merge the commits to master.

LGTM. 

Both 9.4 and 9.5 worked without the madlib.array_agg function - I suggest we delete it as part of this commit. None of the MADlib functions use it anyways (except LDA which was been fixed here). 

@snaga I can do the deletion along with the merge if you're OK.
